The possibility of the ballots in Michoacán individual auszuzählen will be considered
According to the information provided by PREP, the difference between the first and second place in the election of the governor just 27 percent, with 879 votes from a total of 6074 have not yet been counted.
The possibility of individual counting of the ballots in this year's elections in Michoacán a reality, because the Preliminares oral Programa de Resultados Electorales Preliminares (PREP) issued data is the difference between the first and second place in the gubernatorial elections nearly 27 percent, with 879 votes not yet counted a total yet been counted.
In this sense, the President of the Consejo General del Instituto Electoral de Michoacán (IEM), María de los Ángeles Llanderal Zaragoza, recalled that just adopted last November 9, the election of a series of regulations on the harmonisation of local rules with the reforms of the federal states in Electoral matters.
It should be remembered that Michoacán neither his political constitution nor his electoral law nor its law on the election of justice had adapted to the reforms adopted by Congress, so that they in this round were in force, but the governor Leonel Godoy Rangel avoided their publication in the Gazette within the deadlines with the argument that have any objections.
On 9 November, the Supreme Court of Mexico (SCJN) on the constitutional complaint filed by the local legislature and, the voice of the State Ombudsman on the constitutional reforms as "invalid and illegal" because it does not have the right to "decide or a veto against it."
María de los Ángeles Llanderal said in an interview about the possibility of a single count of the votes that, thanks to the adoption of the directives by the Consejo General del IEM now the possibility that the local election authority, the ballot papers partially or completely auszählen.
Under the following conditions in one or more electoral packages contained votes will be counted partial results in the protocols do not agree; the protocol on the counting of and calculation is not an excessive or it is not in possession of the chairman of the electoral commission or there are obvious errors or amendments in the protocols.
In addition, the total count of the total ausgefüllten ballot papers will be carried out if there is a difference between the presumed winner and the second place is the same or less than one percent, provided at the beginning of the session is an explicit request from the party or coalition chairman, the second of the candidates.
The counting of votes can also be carried out in its entirety, if it is after completion of the proper calculation that the difference between the presumed winner and the candidate on the second place equal to or less than one percent, provided that there is an explicit request from a representative of the party, whose candidate has become the second. In this case, the election packages were exposed to a partial recount were excluded.
It is worth noting that the elections in Morelia in the same situation, where, according to PREP the difference between the first and second place just under 0.16%, even though the votes of 129 of a total of 923 election protocols have not yet been counted.
